+## Remote File System Commands
+
+When connected to a remote server, the following commands are available under the `server` group for managing files on the server's sandboxed file system:
+
+| Command | Description | Key Flags |
+|---------|-------------|-----------|
+| `server ls [path]` | List directory contents | `--long` (`-l`), `--recursive`, `--sort name\|size\|modified`, `--reverse` |
+| `server mkdir <path>` | Create a directory | `--parents` (`-p`) |
+| `server rm <path>` | Remove files or directories | `--recursive` (`-r`), `--directory` (`-d`), `--force` (`-f`) |
+| `server mv <source> <dest>` | Move or rename a file/directory | `--force` (`-f`) |
+| `server cp <source> <dest>` | Copy a file or directory | `--recursive` (`-r`), `--force` (`-f`) |
+| `server cat <path>` | Display file contents | `--lines` (`-n`), `--tail` (`-t`), `--force` (`-f`) |
+| `server stat <path>` | Display file or directory information | ΓÇö |
+
+All commands support glob patterns (e.g., `*.txt`, `data?.json`) where applicable. Path traversal outside the server's storage root is blocked.
